			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> paper:</span><br><i>TouchRAM: A Multitouch-Enabled Tool for Aspect-Oriented Software Design</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/WisamAlAbed.html">Wisam Al Abed</a>, <a href="../profile/ValentinBonnet.html">Valentin Bonnet</a>, <a href="../profile/MatthiasSchöttle.html">Matthias Schöttle</a>, <a href="../profile/EnginYıldırım.html">Engin Yıldırım</a>, <a href="../profile/OmarAlam.html">Omar Alam</a>, <a href="../profile/JörgKienzle.html">Jörg Kienzle</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_16">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_16</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is an interactive, multitouch visualization and manipulation environment for aspect-oriented design models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> Multitouch interaction is motivated by improving human usability of complex design operations and model manipulation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It is a concrete tool implementation that supports editing/analysis workflows for aspect-oriented modeling.
</li></ul></li></ul>
